# Complexity Analysis

### Time Complexity

```text
O(n)
```

Every node is visited exactly once.

---

### Space Complexity

```text
O(n)
```

The queue may store all the nodes of one level.

---

# Common Mistakes

### ❌ Mistake 1

Counting only the existing nodes.

The problem asks you to count the **positions**, including missing (`null`) nodes.

---

### ❌ Mistake 2

Forgetting to normalize the indexes.

```java
curIndex = current.index - min;
```

Without normalization, indexes can become extremely large for deep trees.

---

### ❌ Mistake 3

Using

```java
2 * current.index + 1
```

after normalization.

Always generate child indexes using the **normalized index (`curIndex`)**.

---

### ❌ Mistake 4

Calculating width using

```java
queue.size()
```

The width is **not** the number of nodes.

Always calculate

```java
last - first + 1
```

---

# Pattern Recognition

Whenever a tree problem asks about:

* Maximum Width
* Width including missing nodes
* Complete Binary Tree positions

Think:

```text
Level Order BFS

+

Assign Index to Every Node

+

Width = lastIndex - firstIndex + 1
```

